被這些軟弱的理智道德工具所束縛
Surrounding yourself with all these feeble tools of reason.

573
00:39:28,850 --> 00:39:30,750
但父親  他們可能是無辜的
But, father, they might have been innocent.

574
00:39:30,820 --> 00:39:31,880
無辜
Innocent?

575
00:39:32,630 --> 00:39:33,930
他們哪里無辜了
Innocent of what?

576
00:39:34,940 --> 00:39:37,470
這一家人是出了名的流氓無賴
The family is well-known as wastrels and curs.

577
00:39:37,470 --> 00:39:39,190
他們沒有經過審判  檢查
They had no trial, no examination.

578
00:39:39,190 --> 00:39:40,630
他們將會在最偉大
And they shall receive their trial

579
00:39:40,630 --> 00:39:43,550
最仁慈的法官面前接受審判
before the greatest and most merciful of judges.

580
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:49,340
如果他們真是無辜的
Indeed if they are deemed to be innocent,

581
00:39:49,340 --> 00:39:52,500
我相信上帝會好好回報他們的
I trust the lord will see to their recompense.

582
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:53,910
但你
But you...

583
00:39:55,850 --> 00:39:58,910
你的智商都去哪了
you -- have you turned imbecile?

584
00:39:59,570 --> 00:40:03,600
你做的一切只是埋下了致命的懷疑之種
All you do is sow the deadly seeds of doubt.

585
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:06,300
難道你不知道
Do you not see,

586
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:08,590
當追捕巫師時
when hunting witches,

587
00:40:08,590 --> 00:40:11,410
寧可殺死一百個無辜者
far better a hundred innocents die

588
00:40:11,410 --> 00:40:15,420
也絕不能放過一個巫師
than a single solitary witch walks free?

589
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:16,390
知道嗎
Yes!

590
00:40:19,670 --> 00:40:20,810
現在給我坐下
Now, sit you down.

591
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:24,770
好好想想你的過錯
Consider your mistakes.

592
00:40:26,660 --> 00:40:27,660
坐下
Sit.

593
00:40:54,180 --> 00:40:55,330
你要去哪
Where are you going?

594
00:40:56,670 --> 00:40:58,770
這個時候也沒人能讓你燒了
There's no one left to burn at this hour.

595
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:03,820
注意言辭  孩子
Watch your tongue, boy.

596
00:41:05,450 --> 00:41:09,840
難道你以為如今我就不敢拿鞭子抽你了嗎
You think you're too old to be whipped by your father, hmm?

597
00:41:40,230 --> 00:41:41,580
你來遲了
You're too late.

598
00:41:44,270 --> 00:41:46,530
我還以為你會來拯救我們
I thought you were going to save us.

599
00:41:49,630 --> 00:41:52,620
但或許我們根本不值得被救
But maybe we just don't deserve saving.

600
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:06,930
我得承認  這是幅上佳的異教徒之作
It's a pretty piece of paganism, I'll grant you.

601
00:42:09,670 --> 00:42:11,890
但恐怕不太適合公之于眾
But not fit for public viewing.

602
00:42:13,830 --> 00:42:16,440
所以我將它掛在了臥室
That is why it enlightens my bedroom,

603
00:42:17,220 --> 00:42:20,420
只有我至親至愛之人才能得見
where only my nearest and dearest are allowed.

604
00:42:21,670 --> 00:42:24,500
比如你  親愛的英克里斯
Like you, my dear Increase.

605
00:42:25,020 --> 00:42:27,550
你不知道見到你對我來說意味著什么
I can't tell you what it means to see you.

606
00:42:28,230 --> 00:42:30,260
倫敦的皇家法庭如何
How was London and the King's Court?

607
00:42:30,260 --> 00:42:33,180
一如既往地腐敗
Corrupt, as always.

608
00:42:33,910 --> 00:42:37,500
國王批準了我們的新憲章
The king has granted us a new charter,

609
00:42:37,500 --> 00:42:41,480
給予我們選擇之地的所有權力
full claim on this chosen land of ours,

610
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:44,360
他還答應春季便會給我們指派一位新的長官
and he promises a new governor in the spring,

611
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:46,170
一位精通戰術之人
a man experienced in warfare,

612
00:42:46,180 --> 00:42:50,110
來助我們驅逐并根除那些異端匪徒
to help us purge and eradicate the heathen savages

613
00:42:50,110 --> 00:42:53,280
永遠地斬除他們
in our midst for now and forever.

614
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:55,150
看來你真是不虛此行
What a tremendous victory for you.

615
00:42:55,470 --> 00:42:56,450
對我們來說都是
For all of us.

616
00:42:56,930 --> 00:42:58,040
確實
Indeed.

617
00:42:58,500 --> 00:43:00,730
當我踏上歸途時  心中充滿了喜悅
When I set sail for home, I was full of elation.

618
00:43:00,730 --> 00:43:03,870
仿佛僅憑希望便能載我回家
I could have sailed on my hopes alone.

619
00:43:04,790 --> 00:43:06,610
我早該預料到那些邪惡力量
I should have known that the forces of evil

620
00:43:06,610 --> 00:43:09,420
會前來阻撓我
would try to hinder me.

621
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,230
誰
Who? 

622
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:12,130
法國人派來的奸細嗎
Agents of the French?

623
00:43:12,940 --> 00:43:14,030
巫師
Witches.

624
00:43:14,980 --> 00:43:16,800
當然了  他們竭盡全力
Of course, they did all they could.

625
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:19,280
靜止了海風  困住了帆船
They stilled the winds and trapped the ship.

626
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:23,040
四處傳播疾病與異議
They spread disease and dissent all around.

627
00:43:24,140 --> 00:43:25,340
許多人死了
Many died.

628
00:43:27,090 --> 00:43:28,880
但他們不會白白死去
But they did not die in vain.

629
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:30,890
感謝上帝你能平安歸來
Praise god you made it

630
00:43:31,420 --> 00:43:35,650
為我們這個烏云籠罩的小鎮帶來一絲曙光
and landed safely on our shores to lighten our benighted town,

631
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:39,560
就像沉沉黑夜之后重現的耀眼太陽
like the sun returning after the darkest of nights.

632
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:40,950
瑪麗·西布里
Mary Sibley,

633
00:43:41,770 --> 00:43:43,580
無論黑夜多深
However dark the night,

634
00:43:45,090 --> 00:43:49,850
也遮掩不了你雙眸的光芒
your eyes still shine so brightly.

635
00:43:52,100 --> 00:43:54,070
我依然堅信  就算保守病痛侵蝕
You know, I do believe my good friend George,

636
00:43:54,070 --> 00:43:57,900
我的好友喬治仍然是塞勒姆最幸運的男人
for all his suffering, is the luckiest man in Salem.

637
00:43:59,270 --> 00:44:03,740
這么說起來  我很想見見我這位好友
And speaking of my friend, I should like to see him.

638
00:44:03,740 --> 00:44:04,470
可以嗎
May I?

639
00:44:04,470 --> 00:44:06,090
他如今狀況很糟
He is particularly unwell.

640
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:08,120
好不容易  他現在終于睡著了
Thankfully, he's resting at present.

641
00:44:08,730 --> 00:44:10,040
不如你明天再來
You must return tomorrow.

642
00:44:10,590 --> 00:44:13,160
我相信你的到來一定會讓他無比開心的
I'm sure the very sight of you will cheer him immensely,

643
00:44:13,170 --> 00:44:14,280
就像我一樣
As it has me.

644
00:44:14,570 --> 00:44:17,100
您的到來對深陷黑暗的塞勒姆人民來說
Your presence in Salem can only be a tonic

645
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:20,020
真是一劑救命良藥
for all of us in these dark times.

646
00:44:27,530 --> 00:44:30,360
不知此次您會在鎮上停留多久呢
How long may we enjoy your curative presence in town?

647
00:44:32,100 --> 00:44:33,020
這個嘛
Why...

648
00:44:36,250 --> 00:44:38,870
直到我見證那些惡魔的妓女
...until every last devil's whore of a witch

649
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:41,780
塞勒姆最后一個巫師死去
in Salem is dead.

